solution: ```class Solution {
    public int minSteps(String s, String t) {
        int[] freq = new int[26];
        for (char c : s.toCharArray()) freq[c - 'a']++;
        int steps = 0;
        for (char c : t.toCharArray()) {
            if (freq[c - 'a'] > 0) freq[c - 'a']--;
            else steps++;
        }
        return steps;
    }
}```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Count character frequencies in s, then for each character in t decrement the count if it exists; otherwise the character must be replaced. The number of unmatched characters equals the minimal replacements needed.

